Now I have a complete and accurate picture. NOHASH is used by proxy/fastcgi/grpc/upstream/gzip for variables like `$proxy_host`, `$proxy_port`, `$upstream_addr` etc. — these are registered but NOT put in the runtime hash, so they can ONLY be accessed via their index (i.e., when explicitly referenced via `$name` in config, which triggers `ngx_http_get_variable_index` at config time → indexed). The point: they won't be found by a runtime by-name lookup (e.g., `ngx_http_get_variable` with an arbitrary name), avoiding hash pollution and ensuring they're only computed when actually used.

WEAK is used by rewrite module (`set $var ...` creates a weak variable) — a weak variable is one that, if not "strengthened" by an explicit `ngx_http_add_variable` without WEAK, will be treated as not_found. Actually from the code: in init_vars at 2824-2827, `if (av->get_handler == NULL || (av->flags & NGX_HTTP_VAR_WEAK)) { break; }` — this means a WEAK variable (with no real get_handler) doesn't get the `goto next`, so it falls through to the prefix-variable check and then the "unknown variable" check. Wait, let me re-read.

Actually the logic in init_vars for indexed variables: for each indexed variable v[i] (in cmcf->variables array), it searches variables_keys for a matching name. If found (av), it copies av's get_handler/data, marks av as INDEXED, sets av->index = i. Then `if (av->get_handler == NULL || (av->flags & NGX_HTTP_VAR_WEAK)) break;` else `goto next`. 

The `break` here breaks out of the inner `for n` loop (searching keys), NOT the outer loop. So after break, it continues to `len = 0; av = NULL;` and the prefix-variable search. Wait no — after the `break`, control goes to line 2834 `len = 0; av = NULL;` which resets and searches prefix variables. Hmm, that doesn't seem right because we already found a match.

Wait, let me re-read more carefully:

```c
for (i = 0; i < cmcf->variables.nelts; i++) {
    for (n = 0; n < cmcf->variables_keys->keys.nelts; n++) {
        av = key[n].value;
        if (v[i].name.len == key[n].key.len && ngx_strncmp(...) == 0) {
            v[i].get_handler = av->get_handler;
            v[i].data = av->data;
            av->flags |= NGX_HTTP_VAR_INDEXED;
            v[i].flags = av->flags;
            av->index = i;
            if (av->get_handler == NULL || (av->flags & NGX_HTTP_VAR_WEAK)) {
